NodeJS
-
     - NodeJS is the Server Side Scripting Language.

     - By using NodeJS , we can create the Servers (http & tcp)

     - As a Node Developer , we can assign the port number to the Servers.

Modules in NodeJS.

1.mysql

     - this module used to interact with the mysql database.

2.mongodb

     - this module used to interact with the mongodb.

3.express

    - this module used to develop the Rest API.

4. body-parser

    - it is used to set the MIME Type.
    Ex.
        json
        xml
        text
        --
        --
        --

5. http
      - it is used to create the http servers.

6.fs
      - it is used to interact with the file system.
      Ex.
        text files
        xml files
        json files
        --
        --
7.jwt-simple
    - it is used to maintain the token based authentication system

